    "We clustered these using the K-means method (classification with 16 clusters) and compressed the results into two dimensions using the uniform manifold approximation and projection (UMAP) technique (McInnes et al., 2018) (Fig. 2).",
    "Figures 3 compares the distribution of papers and patents in the same science-technology space as one of Fig. 2, between papers/patents published/applied in 1990s and those in the 2010s, where the red indicates the location of patents, while the blue indicates the location of research papers.",
    "Overall, a large percentage of the research papers were related to life science (cells/ genes, medicine) and chemistry/materials (chemical compounds, metal ingredients).",
    "They were evidently distributed across the fields of optics, fluid processing, and video display.",
    "However, fields relating to mechanics (motion control, structural mechanics, and thermodynamics), electronic devices, and image processing are mostly covered by patents."
